               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_109253">Drayton</placeName>.
      

                        <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Deye</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>, chaplain</persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Rose</surname>
                        </persName> grant to <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename>, prior</persName>, &amp;c., of <orgName key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </orgName> all the land in <placeName key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName> and <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName> which they had of the gift of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Snow</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Roberd</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, viz. (i) 4 strips of the gift of J<supplied>ohn</supplied> S<supplied>now</supplied> in the east field of <placeName key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName>—two lying by the <placeName type="minor">Redewell over le Middelfurlong</placeName>, between the land late of <persName>
                           <forename>Agnes</forename> 
                           <surname>Martyn</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108031">Welton</placeName>
                        </persName> and that late of <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Fyscher</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>
                        </persName>; and two reach to <placeName type="minor">Tunslade</placeName>, between the land of the said Agnes, and that of <persName>
                           <forename>Alice</forename> 
                           <surname>Cumfray</surname>
                        </persName>; (ii) ½ an acre in <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName> of the gift of Thomas, lying over <placeName type="minor">le Rowfurlong</placeName> by the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> of <surname>D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </surname>
                        </persName>; (iii) a rent of 3/- which they had of the gift of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> le <surname>Warde</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108032">Westhaddon</placeName>
                        </persName>. For 30 years. 
   Given at <placeName role="date" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName>. 
   Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Symond</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>pistrino</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Staverton</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Werrour</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> 
                           <surname>Porter</surname>
                        </persName> of the same. 
   <origDate when="1349-02-06">
                           <supplied>6 Feb. 1349.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
